  <li>Appearances donâ€™t matter, Environment doesnâ€™t matter
  This sense of invulnerability to emotional / cultural impact due to a belief in oneâ€™s own rationality</li>
  <li>Chestertonâ€™s Fence
  The absence of understanding something is conflated with the misunderstood object being useless. An important instance of the overconfidence that comes out of naive rationality. 
  Two reformers find a fence in their way. The first doesnâ€™t see the fenceâ€™s purpose, so he goes to knock it down. The second says that until the first reformer can see the purpose of the fence, he wonâ€™t allow him to knock it down.</li>
  <li>Goodhartâ€™s Law
